            "text": "—Heb., ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "then he chose,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " the construction being changed after the parenthesis.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Solomon my son.—The son who has the best right to the name. (Comp. 1Chronicles 22:10.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Solomon my son.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The son who has the best right to the name. (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 22:10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The throne of the kingdom of the Lord.—This expression is unique in the Old Testament. (Comp. 1Chronicles 29:23; 1Chronicles 17:14.) It brings out into strong relief the idea that the Israelite monarchy was only a vicegerency; not David nor Solomon, but Jehovah being the true and only King. (Comp. Gideon’s reply to the offer of the crown, Judges 8:23; 1Samuel 8:7; 1Samuel 12:12.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The throne of the kingdom of the Lord.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—This expression is unique in the Old Testament. (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 29:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
