            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 17:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".) It brings out into strong relief the idea that the Israelite monarchy was only a vicegerency; not David nor Solomon, but Jehovah being the true and only King. (Comp. Gideon’s reply to the offer of the crown, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Judges 8:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
